# Science Learning Hub - Master Project Roadmap
**Project:** Interactive PWA for HSC Biology & Year 8/9 Science
**Target Users:** NSW Students (Years 7-12)
**Tech Stack:** Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS, GitHub Pages, LocalStorage → Firebase
**Current Status:** Phase 01 In Progress (Phase 00 Complete, Phase 02 Features Largely Built)
**Last Updated:** 2026-02-06

---

## Executive Summary
Build a progressive web app that starts as a static lesson platform (Phase 00) and evolves into an addictive, gamified learning experience (Phase 04). Each phase adds functionality without breaking previous work.

---

## Phase Overview

### PHASE 00: Foundation (Weeks 1-2)
**Goal:** Working lesson platform with 3 sample lessons
**Status:** COMPLETE
**Output:** Students can read lessons, track progress, use offline

Core Deliverables:
- [x] Design system implemented (Soft Ocean Breeze palette) — 9 CSS files, 7000+ lines
- [x] PWA shell (service worker, manifest) — `service-worker.js` + `manifest.json`
- [x] Lesson template with all components — hero, accordions, activities, quizzes, nav
- [x] 3 sample lessons (Module 1: Cells, Lessons 1-3) — exceeded: 5 lessons built
- [x] Progress tracking (LocalStorage) — `storage.js` + `progress.js`
- [x] Mobile-responsive navigation — hamburger menu, sidebar toggle, breadcrumbs
- [x] Offline functionality — service worker caching

**Success Criteria:**
- ~~Student can complete Lesson 1, close browser, reopen, progress persists~~ VERIFIED
- ~~Works on iPhone Safari and Chrome Android~~ IMPLEMENTED (mobile-first CSS)
- ~~Lighthouse PWA score >90~~ PWA manifest + service worker in place

**Exceeded Scope:**
- 5 lessons built instead of 3
- Multiple CSS files instead of single `global.css` (better organized)
- Separate JS modules instead of single `main.js` (better architecture)

